The paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The algorithm proposed in the paper is designed to perform efficient exploration-exploitation in Markov decision processes, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and analysis of the algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with control and decision-making in systems, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
